  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-low heat with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and <strong>half</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>of the<strong> truffle oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-brie-black-pepper-and-truffle-linguine/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to turn very slightly golden</p><p>Once done, transfer to <strong>kitchen paper</strong> (use a fork to get them out of the oil) and set aside</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – these are your <strong>truffled garlic crisps</strong></p><p>Reserve the pan and the oil</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-brie-black-pepper-and-truffle-linguine/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> </strong>linguine for 7-9 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the linguine, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-brie-black-pepper-and-truffle-linguine/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the linguine is cooking, chop the <strong>brie </strong>into small pieces</p><p>Peel the <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> until you end up with a pile of cheese shavings</p><p>Crumble the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-brie-black-pepper-and-truffle-linguine/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>seedless grapes </strong>in half</p><p>Combine the <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong> – this is your<strong> balsamic dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-brie-black-pepper-and-truffle-linguine/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the linguine is cooked, return the reserved pan and oil to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> cracked</strong> <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add 90ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong> with the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(and any<strong> crumbled Italian hard cheese</strong>), <strong>chopped brie</strong> and<strong> crème fraîche</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until everything's melted and a cheese sauce has formed</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-brie-black-pepper-and-truffle-linguine/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained linguine</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and stir it all together – this is your<strong> cheesy brie, black pepper & truffle linguine</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>rocket</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> kitchen paper</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-brie-black-pepper-and-truffle-linguine/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cheesy brie, black pepper & truffle linguine </strong>topped with the <strong>cheese shavings</strong> and <strong>truffled garlic crisps</strong></p><p>Drizzle the<strong> remaining truffle oil </strong>all over and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Toss the <strong>rocket</strong> and<strong> grapes</strong> together and drizzle with the<strong> balsamic dressing</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
